<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 06 at 7:08PM PDT  by NWS Pendleton</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Umatilla and southwestern Union Counties through 745 PM PDT...
At 707 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lehman Hot Springs, or 28 miles southwest of Meacham, moving east at
45 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ukiah, Lehman Hot Springs and Starkey.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
